* Illusion Interactive *
* IGS-term

IGS is a server for online games. IGS-term is a client terminal 
created to connect/control IGS.

Start IGS-term :
	$ igsterm
	
	or
	
	$ igst

Quit IGS-term :
	$ exit

Connect an IGS server :
	$ igst.connect(host,port)

Disconnect an IGS server :
	$ exit

Shortcut to server :
	$ igst.add_server(host,port)
	Create a new server shortcut
	
	$ igst.rm_server(host,port)
	Remove a server from shortcut list
	
	To use a shortcut, enter its number on the
	IGS command line.
	Example : 	1. localhost:21
			2. 192.168.1.10:5412
			...
	Enter "1" to connect localhost:21

Other commands :
	$ igst.ls_servers()
	Update server list and show the shortcut list
	
	$ igst.home_path()
	Create /.illusion/igsterm in the HOME directory 
	if not exist.
	
	$ igst.init()
	Re-initialize IGS-term.

Licence command :
	$ show w
	Print disclaimenr and warranty on the terminal
	
	$ show c
	Print condition and licence on the terminal
	
